"9/20/1994--Introduced. Declares that the Senate: (1) commends the efforts of the President in sending former President Jimmy Carter, retired General Colin Powell, and Senator Sam Nunn to Haiti to avoid the loss of American lives; (2) supports the U.S. armed forces in Haiti who are performing with excellence and patriotism; (3) supports the departure from power of the de facto authorities there and Haitian efforts to return democracy; (4) supports lifting of U.S. unilateral economic sanctions and U.N. resolutions supporting such sanctions; and (5) supports the withdrawal of U.S. armed forces as soon as possible."